                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Auditory",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 453,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 38,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "d108d452587889359960cb6377f62982",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Curse",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 454,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "A curse is an effect that places some long-term affliction on a creature. Curses are always magical and are typically the result of a spell or trap. Effects with this trait can be removed only by effects that specifically target curses.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 101,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
